<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-29T11:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-29T11:40:00-05:00" n="292" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d292">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1186.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Henry</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Puerto Plata</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-29T12:00:00-04:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 29, 1914, noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I had an interview with Bordas this morning. He declares that Puerto
                            Plata is blockaded, he will continue to use cannon against the town but
                            promises care. Do not believe Government has much more than thousand
                            soldiers Cibao and four hundred attacking here. The situation unchanged.
                            Gunboat is essential for the protection of foreigners. English have
                            requested one.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>